history.content: You cannot P/NP one of those courses as you won't have completed your graduation requirements when you take them (you only get the units for a course once you pass the final exam).

children.subject:
I understand that, but like I said, you cannot P/NP until you have completed the requirements. You get the units only if you pass the class. What you're suggesting cannot be done as it would actually be before you fulfill the requirements since there is no guarantee that you'd get those 4 units you need (what if you fail that class, get caught for academic dishonesty, etc.)

Either way, I'd advise you to talk to your advisor and discuss your situation.
yea but what if I don't WANT one of those courses to count to my graduation requirements at all?

history.content: We are in the final stages of approval to reduce that 45 units requirement to 40 units. The final sign off is expected in early June, and then it will be announced. Obviously until official, it's not guaranteed.

children.subject: If the 45 Engineering Units were reduced to 40 Engineering Units would that apply to Spring 2019 grads as well?

history.content: By the end of this semester, Spring 18, I will have accrued 44 total engineering units, and will have completed the minimum 20 units of Upper Division EECS units. Next semester I am planning to take EECS149 and CS168, two 4 unit courses. Can I P/NP one of these courses, even though I don't have 45 total engineering units? All my other requirements, except for natural science elective, are also complete.
history.subject: P/NP With 44 Engineering Units
